The paper focuses on collision management and safety of mobile robots and robotic manipulators operating in human environments, which is a key area of research in robotics. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also discusses the use of motion planning, probabilistic reasoning methods, and sensor processing, which are all areas of research in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and control systems (cs.SY). The paper also mentions the use of real-time sensing and control systems, which could fall under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories.
